WorkItem.Description:
Hi, I just noticed that in SvgText.cs in method MeasureString(..) there needs to be a null check on "text" otherwise
the System.Drawing.Drawing2D.GraphicsPath.AddString(..) method throws a null reference exception.
 
This is my suggested fix, but I am not really sure if 0 breaks other things that is why I am posting it here:
 
static private int MeasureString(SvgRenderer renderer, string text, Font font)
        {
            if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(text))
                return 0;
 
            GraphicsPath p = new GraphicsPath();
            p.AddString(text, font.FontFamily, 0, font.Size, new PointF(0.0f, 0.0f), StringFormat.GenericTypographic);
            p.Transform(renderer.Transform);
            return (int)(p.GetBounds().Width + 1.0f);
        }
 
Thanks,
Erion
